Why CC BY-SA 4.0
----------------

The core value of this project is the curated dataset and AI evaluations,
not the thin UI layer that displays them. CC BY-SA's ShareAlike clause
matches this project's "AI as third-party evaluator, community-improvable"
model: anyone publishing improved evaluations is required to publish them
back under the same terms, keeping the dataset a community resource.

Note: Creative Commons does not recommend CC licenses for software in
general (no patent grant, no source / object distinction). We accept that
trade-off because (a) this code base contains no novel algorithms or
patentable inventions, (b) it is a single web application where source IS
deployment, and (c) anyone reusing this code is almost certainly building
a comparable roadmap, which is exactly the case ShareAlike is meant to
cover.

